        <abstract> 
<p>Thanks for EK’s book [<hi rend="italic">Werden und Vergehen</hi> (1876)].</p> 
            <p>Regrets he cannot write for EK’s journal, but his son, Francis, may do so.</p> 
<p>Suggests EK as editor urge on readers [of <hi rend="italic">Kosmos</hi>] the investigation of the causes of variability; why, for instance, do wild Pampas cattle change colour when domesticated? Thinks experiments and observations on recently domesticated animals and cultivated plants would throw light on the subject.</p> 
        </abstract>
